<!-- ── ORIGIN STORY ── -->
<section class="section about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <p class="section-label">Our Origin</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Where it all begins</h2>
        <p class="section-body">In many traditions across cultures, a healer's breath carries power to bless, cleanse, and restore. The act of blowing — the <em>phook</em> — is one of the oldest gestures of intention in human history. A breath toward fire. A breath across seed. A breath onto the hands before work begins.</p>
        <div class="pull-quote">"Truth has breath. This is it."</div>
        <p class="section-body">Phook Theory is built on that single ancient idea. Not as a spiritual claim, but as a practical truth: what you breathe into, you breathe life into. What you hold your breath from, you starve. The exhale is where your power lives — not in the holding.</p>
      </div>
